individual compound|women's individual compound]] event.<ref name=\"belarus_k2_500m_minsk_2019\">{{Cite news|last=Rowbottom|first=Mike|url=https://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/1081276/belarus-k2-500m-canoe-sprint-pair-beat-hungarys-world-champions-to-gold-at-minsk-2019|title=Belarus K2 500m canoe sprint pair beat Hungary\u2019s world champions to gold at Minsk 2019|date=26 June 2019|work=InsideTheGames.biz|access-date=5 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"ellison_outshoots_minsk_2019\">{{Cite news|last=Stanley|first=John|url=https://worldarchery.org/news/171268/ellison-outshoots-world-champion-inaugural-compound-womens-title-european-games-1|title=Ellison outshoots world champion to inaugural compound women\u2019s title at European Games|date=26 June 2019|work=World Archery|access-date=5 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2017, she won the silver medal in the [[Archery at the 2017 World Games|women's individual compound]] event at the [[2017 World Games]] held in Wroc\u0142aw, Poland.\n\nIn 2019, alongside Sta\u0161 Modic, she won a silver medal in the mixed team event at the [[2019 Archery World Cup|Archery World Cup]] in Berlin.\n\n== Personal life ==\n\nEllison was born and raised in Ljubljana, Slovenia.<ref name=\"toja_ellison_better_person_2017\">{{Cite web|url=https://worldarchery.org/news/149722/toja-ellison-my-plan-become-better-person|title=Toja Ellison: My plan is to become a better person|date=23 June 2017|website=World Archery|url-status=live|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref> In April 2016, she married [[Recurve bow|recurve]] archer [[Brady Ellison]].<ref name=\"toja_ellison_better_person_2017\"/>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commonscat}}\n* {{World Archery}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ellison, Toja}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Slovenian female archers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Ljubljana\u200e]]\n[[Category:Archers at the 2019 European Games]]\n[[Category:European Games competitors for Slovenia]]\n[[Category:European Games medalists in archery]]\n[[Category:European Games gold medalists for Slovenia]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 2017 World Games]]\n[[Category:World Games silver medalists]]\n\n\n{{Slovenia-archery-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Slovenian archer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| honorific_prefix = \n| name             = Toja Ellison\n| honorific_suffix = \n| image            = 2019-09-06 - Archery World Cup Final - Women's Compound - Toja Ellison.jpg\n| image_size       = <!-- only when absolutely necessary -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = Ellison in 2019\n| headercolor      = \n| textcolor        = \n<!-- Personal information -->\n| native_name      = \n| native_name_lang = \n| birth_name       = Toja \u010cerne<!-- if different than name -->\n| full_name        = <!-- if different than name/birth_name -->\n| nickname         = \n| nationality      = <!-- will not display if national_team is defined -->\n| national_team    = <!-- only for the country represented in international competition -->\n| ethnicity        = \n| citizenship      = \n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1993|7|4}}\n| birth_place      = Ljubljana, Slovenia\n| death_date       = <!-- {{death date and age|death year|death month|death day|birth year|birth month|birth day}} -->\n| death_place      = \n| resting_place    = \n| resting_place_coordinates = \n| monuments        = \n| residence        = \n| hometown         = \n| education        = \n| alma_mater       = \n| occupation       = \n| years_active     = \n| employer         = \n| agent            = \n| height           = <!-- X cm, X m, or X ft Y in (automatic conversion) plus optional year and reference -->\n| weight           = <!-- X kg, X lb, or X st Y lb (automatic conversion) plus optional year and reference -->\n| spouse           = [[Brady Ellison]]\n| life_partner     = \n| other_interests  = \n| website   