ister |first=Sean |date=2 December 2008 |website=GameCyte |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090309204615/http://www.gamecyte.com/riddick-dark-athena-is-remake-no-more |archive-date=9 March 2009 |url-status=dead |access-date=2 December 2008}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Sid Meier's Colonization]]''\n|[[DOS]]\n|''[[Civilization IV: Colonization]]''\n|Microsoft Windows, Mac OS X\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2008/09/26/sid-meiers-civilization-iv-colonization-review |title=Sid Meier's Colonization IV: Colonization review  |last=Butts |first=Steve |date=26 September 2008 |website=[[IGN]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170601104041/http://www.ign.com/articles/2008/09/26/sid-meiers-civilization-iv-colonization-review |archive-date=1 June 2017 |url-status=live |access-date=1 June 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Comic Party]]'' || Microsoft Windows, [[Dreamcast]]\n|''Comic Party Portable'' || PlayStation Portable\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mobygames.com/game/comic-party-portable |title=Comic Party Portable for PSP (2005) |website=[[MobyGames]] |access-date=7 July 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan= \"2\" | ''[[Command & Conquer (1995 video game)|Command & Conquer]]''\n|rowspan= \"2\" | DOS, Mac OS, Microsoft Windows\n|''Command & Conquer 64'' || [[Nintendo 64]]; it utilizes 3D rendered models\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/1999/06/30/command-conquer-2 |title=Command & Conquer |last=Boulding |first=Aaron |date=29 June 1999 |website=[[IGN]] |access-date=4 August 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|''Command & Conquer: Gold'' || Microsoft Windows; it features an enhanced graphical engine for [[Windows 95]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.zdnet.com/gamespot/features/all/real_time/index.html |title=GameSpot Presents: A History of Real-Time Strategy Games |last=Geryk |first=Bruce |website=[[GameSpot]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20010405012159/http://www.zdnet.com/gamespot/features/all/real_time/index.html |archive-date=5 April 2001 |access-dat